\(k\)

cross_valid <- function(df, k){
  ##
  idx <- sample(1:k, nrow(df), replace = TRUE)
  rmse_train <- c()
  rmse_test <- c()
  ##k
  for (i in 1:k){
    ##
    data_train <- df[idx != i, ]
    data_test <- df[idx == i, ]
    ##
    fit <- lm(~., data_train)
    ##
    pred <- predict(fit, data_test)
    ##RMSE()
    rmse_train <- c(rmse_train, sqrt(mean((fit$fitted.values - data_train$) ^ 2)))
    rmse_test <- c(rmse_test, sqrt(mean((pred - data_test$) ^ 2)))
  }
  ##kRMSERMSE
  structure(list(rmse_train = rmse_train, rmse_test = rmse_test))
}

rmse <- c()
rmse_df <- data.frame('time' = NA, 'type' = NA, 'rmse' = NA)
##
set.seed(1)
for (j in 1:50){
  result <- cross_valid(data[, -c(3, 6, 7)], 5)
  ##RMSE
  rmse_df <- rbind(na.omit(rmse_df), data.frame('time' = (j - 1) * 5 + rep(1:5, 2), 'type' = c(rep('', 5), rep('', 5)), 'rmse' = c(result[[1]], result[[2]])))
}
##250RMSE
rmse_train_mean <- mean(rmse_df$rmse[which(rmse_df$type == '')])
rmse_test_mean <- mean(rmse_df$rmse[which(rmse_df$type == '')])
print(paste('50RMSE', rmse_train_mean, '', sep = '')); print(paste('50RMSE', rmse_test_mean, '', sep = ''))
